<div class="col-sm-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1 row" style="padding-top:50px;padding-bottom:30px;">
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 box-centered row">
        <div class="card fluid">
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Minimal Code
                    <small>Less maintenance!</small>
                </h3>
                <img src="${root}/design/feather.svg" id="logo-medium">
                <p><strong>xdocc</strong> is a small application. There are currently
                    less than 3500 lines of code. This is essential to keep the codebase esay to maintain. Most of
                    the functionality comes from third party libraries. A careful decision has been made to only use
                    rock solid mature libraries.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 box-centered row">
        <div class="card fluid">
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Incremental Compiling
                    <small>Speed matters!</small>
                </h3>
                <img src="${root}/design/rocket.svg" id="logo-medium">
                <p><strong>xdocc</strong> compiles incrementally and caches intermediate steps. That means
                    a quick update won't compile the entire site from scratch. It uses file notifications on supported
                    platforms to automatically compile incrementally when a file changes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 box-centered row">
        <div class="card fluid">
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Framework Agnostic
                    <small>Modules and plugins!</small>
                </h3>
                <img src="${root}/design/thumb.svg" id="logo-medium">
                <p><strong>xdocc</strong> can use any front-end web framework (e.g. bootstrap,
                    mini.css, Milligram, Pure.css. It also nicely integrates with single page application
                    frameworks, such as Vue.js, React, or Angular.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 box-centered row">
        <div class="card fluid">
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Supported Formats
                    <small>Static everything!</small>
                </h3>
                <img src="${root}/design/books.svg" id="logo-medium">
                <p><strong>xdocc</strong> supports a wide rang of input formats. The following input formats are
                    supported: Markdown (confluence), Textile,
                    Wiki (media, trac, confluence, t_wiki), plain text, HTML, and images. More input formats can be
                    easily added.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>